Question 1

Discuss the advantages and challenges associated with an open data science approach. Provide an example based on this week’s reading. (1-2 paragraphs)

Open data science approach is an aspect of broader open science movement that can make scientific data and methods openly accessible. It contains sharing data sets, code and other research materials that allows others to access and use.

This has advantages and disadvantages. For example, it allows for greater transparency and reproducibility in research. People from different areas and organizations can share data and code to solve problems faster. And it promotes reproducibility in research. Reducing the probability of bias or errors. Besides, it also foster innovation and creativity. People can develop new methods and create easier.

However, there are some challenges. Sharing data can cause some security risks. We need to develop proper data security to protect the open data. We will face some privacy and ethical concerns due to the open data. Furthermore, open datasets won’t always have high quality resource, there may be problems with missing data.

  ggtitle("The Land Use of Washtenaw County") + ##Give the map a title
    geom_sf(data = boulder, aes(color=LEVEL5),
    fill =NA, alpha = .2) + ## Draw a map by using the LEVEL5 field
    scale_colour_gradientn(colours = viridis(10))+ ## Define the scale color 
   annotation_north_arrow(location = "right")+ ## Add north arrow to map
  annotation_scale()+ ## Add a map scale to map
  annotate("text",x = 278000, y = 4658000, 
  label = "Map layout:Yuxin He;Date:10-29-2023.")##Add the date and author to map

boulder %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=LAND_USE, y= AREA)) + ##set X and Y values 
  geom_bar(stat='identity',fill='orange')+ ##set stat to show original count and fill color
  labs(title="The Areas of Different Land Use types in Whashtenaw",x='Land Use Type', y='Area')+ ##set title and X,Y axes labels
  theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=90)) ##set the rotation of X text to 90 degrees
